HEADWORD: Pimelic
<hw>Pi*mel"ic</hw> <pr>(p⟦icr⟧*m⟦ecr⟧l"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>pimelh`</grk> fat.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a substance obtained from certain
fatty substances, and subsequently shown to be a mixture of suberic and
adipic acids.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Designating the acid proper
(<chform>C5H10(CO2H)2</chform>) which is obtained from camphoric
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pimelite</ent>⟦br⟧
